decision_details:
- The proposal made by Hon. Ranil Wickramasinghe, Minister of Policy Planning, Economic Affairs, Child, Youth and Cultural Affairs to sign a Memorandum of Understanding between the Democratic Socialist Republic of Sri Lanka and the Ministry of Youth Affairs and Sports in the State of Qatar was approved by the Cabinet. This Memorandum of Understanding covers mainly  the following areas.  

*	Promoting the corporation between the two countries for exchange of members of the Youth Organizations, experts and specialists etc., involved in the activities pertaining to youth policies; 

*	Promoting the corporation in physical as well as  economic activities relating to  youth and the exchange of ideas and information relevant to youth development between the two countries; 

*	Promoting the corporation between the two countries by exchanging ideas with regard to youth problems on the results of the field research activities; 

*	Implementation of youth sports, cultural exchange programmes and youth exchange programmes extensively between the two countries; 

*	Promoting corporation regarding the exchange of information pertaining to employment of the unemployed youth community; and 

*	Promoting cooperation between the two countries as agreed upon in the field of youth development.
